<subSubSection lastPageId="175" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="173.[810,1452,260,2093]" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[863,985,441,467]" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Themaleof 
<emphasis box="[1118,1337,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Actinopuspindapoy</emphasis>
resembles those of 
<taxonomicName box="[906,1043,477,503]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itacolomi">
<emphasis box="[906,1043,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. itacolomi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1058,1153,477,504]" captionStart="FIGURE 153" captionStartId="169.[136,235,1379,1403]" captionTargetBox="[161,1413,198,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-264@169.[151,1436,189,1355]" captionTargetPageId="169" captionText="FIGURE 153. Actinopus itacolomi sp. nov., male: A–C IBSP: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D UFMG 18876: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597563/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
A–C), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[1234,1391,477,503]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpis">
<emphasis box="[1234,1391,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. longipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 156" captionStartId="172.[136,235,1679,1703]" captionTargetBox="[188,1382,198,1643]" captionTargetId="figure-114@172.[151,1435,189,1655]" captionTargetPageId="172" captionText="FIGURE 156. Actinopus longipalpis C. L. Koch, 1842, holotype, male: A–E ZMB 2107: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc- Prolateral Accessory keel; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel. D. Rastellum, dorsal; E. Rastellum, ventral. Scales lines: A–C: 1 mm; D–E: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597571/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 156</figureCitation>
A–C), 
<taxonomicName box="[941,1020,514,540]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tutu">
<emphasis box="[941,1020,514,540]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. tutu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1039,1137,513,539]" captionStart="FIGURE 143" captionStartId="158.[136,235,1667,1691]" captionTargetBox="[189,1400,199,1627]" captionTargetId="figure-100@158.[151,1436,189,1643]" captionTargetPageId="158" captionText="FIGURE 143. Actinopus tutu sp. nov., male: A–C UFMG 585: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D UFMG 5647: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597543/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 143</figureCitation>
A–C), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1226,1370,514,540]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus">
<emphasis box="[1226,1370,514,540]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018, fig. 10 G–I), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1267,1374,550,576]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pampa">
<emphasis box="[1267,1374,550,576]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. pampa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018, fig. 27 G–I) and 
<taxonomicName box="[1329,1452,585,612]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azaghal">
<emphasis box="[1329,1452,585,612]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. azaghal</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[818,911,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURE 148" captionStartId="164.[136,235,1656,1680]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,211,1588]" captionTargetId="figure-107@164.[151,1435,189,1633]" captionTargetPageId="164" captionText="FIGURE 148. Actinopus azaghal sp. nov., male: A–C MCTP: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel;Arrow: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D CZUFMT-ARAC: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: Male: 1 mm; Female: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597553/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 148</figureCitation>
A–C) by the presence of three keels in prolateral view of embolus, small total length, and inconspicuous patterns of coloration on legs and palp, when present. It resembles 
<emphasis box="[959,1280,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[959,1123,730,756]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpis">A. longipalpis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1136,1280,730,756]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus">A. argenteus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1341,1451,730,756]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pampa">
<emphasis box="[1341,1451,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. pampa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of serrated area below PAc. They resemble those of 
<emphasis box="[919,1179,802,829]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">
<taxonomicName box="[919,1049,802,829]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azaghal">A. azaghal</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1065,1179,803,829]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pampa">A. pampa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1842" box="[1246,1410,802,829]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpis">
<emphasis box="[1246,1410,802,829]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. longipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by BTA dorsally inserted. It also resembles 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1413,838,865]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="azaghal">A. azaghal</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pampa">A. pampa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[940,1015,875,901]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tutu">
<emphasis box="[940,1015,875,901]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. tutu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by PA continuous to PI. It differs from those of all these species by the very inconspicuous and delicate PAc. It further differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1213,1320,947,973]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pampa">
<emphasis box="[1213,1320,947,973]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. pampa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of depression at embolus base and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1273,1414,983,1009]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="173" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus">
<emphasis box="[1273,1414,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">A. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by BTA inserted at the middle of prolateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="173.[810,1452,260,2093]" lastBlockId="175.[136,778,1327,1727]" lastPageId="175" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">
MALE (MACN-Ar 19824): Total length 13.87; Carapace, long 6.37; wide 6.62. Carapace rounded. Anterior eye row slightly procurved, posterior row recurved (
<figureCitation box="[925,1051,1163,1190]" captionStart="FIGURE 157" captionStartId="174.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,205,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-184@174.[151,1436,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="174" captionText="FIGURE 157. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–F MACN-Ar 19824: A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597573/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 157 B</figureCitation>
). With few short and weak bristles between AME-clypeus, between ALE–ALP, between posterior eyes-fovea and lateral eyes-edge of carapace. Sternum with eight sigilla fused medially, two distal sigilla more fused than others (
<figureCitation box="[1180,1313,1308,1335]" captionStart="FIGURE 157" captionStartId="174.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,205,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-184@174.[151,1436,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="174" captionText="FIGURE 157. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–F MACN-Ar 19824: A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597573/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 157 C</figureCitation>
). Rastellum protuberant, inverted V-shaped, with some short bristles, without spines apically (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1189,1380,1407]" captionStart="FIGURE 157" captionStartId="174.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,205,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-184@174.[151,1436,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="174" captionText="FIGURE 157. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–F MACN-Ar 19824: A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597573/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 157</figureCitation>
E–F). Chelicerae with ten denticles along prolateral row of teeth. Prolateral row with five megateeth and two basal teeth. Retrolateral row with six megateeth and six denticles between the two basal megateeth (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1200,1524,1551]" captionStart="FIGURE 157" captionStartId="174.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,205,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-184@174.[151,1436,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="174" captionText="FIGURE 157. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–F MACN-Ar 19824: A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597573/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 157 D</figureCitation>
). Patella and tibia III with distal crown of well-developed thorns, on patella III interrupted in middle and on tibia III not interrupted in middle (
<figureCitation box="[949,1053,1633,1660]" captionStart="FIGURE 158" captionStartId="175.[136,235,1155,1179]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,205,1116]" captionTargetId="figure-319@175.[151,1436,189,1132]" captionTargetPageId="175" captionText="FIGURE 158. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–D MACN-Ar 19824: A. Patella III, dorsal; B. Tibia III, dorsal; C. Patella IV, dorsal; D. Tibia IV, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597575" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597575/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 158</figureCitation>
A–B). Patellae III and IV with spines on prolaterodorsal face (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1333,1669,1696]" captionStart="FIGURE 158" captionStartId="175.[136,235,1155,1179]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,205,1116]" captionTargetId="figure-319@175.[151,1436,189,1132]" captionTargetPageId="175" captionText="FIGURE 158. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–D MACN-Ar 19824: A. Patella III, dorsal; B. Tibia III, dorsal; C. Patella IV, dorsal; D. Tibia IV, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597575" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597575/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 158 A, C</figureCitation>
). Tibia IV without spines on dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[1211,1346,1705,1732]" captionStart="FIGURE 158" captionStartId="175.[136,235,1155,1179]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,205,1116]" captionTargetId="figure-319@175.[151,1436,189,1132]" captionTargetPageId="175" captionText="FIGURE 158. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–D MACN-Ar 19824: A. Patella III, dorsal; B. Tibia III, dorsal; C. Patella IV, dorsal; D. Tibia IV, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597575" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597575/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 158 D</figureCitation>
). Ventral pseudoscopulae occupying 40% of tarsus I, 50% of II and 100% of III and IV. Pseudoscopula of tarsi I and II with setae spaced, forming diffuse group of bristles; On tarsi III and IV, compact. Carapace, chelicerae, sternum, coxae, trochantera, femora, patellae, tibiae, metatarsi and tarsi reddish brown; tibia of palp orangish brown, paler than other articles; Abdomen bluish pale gray, with many unpigmented spots (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1161,1994,2021]" captionStart="FIGURE 157" captionStartId="174.[136,235,1645,1669]" captionTargetBox="[175,1412,205,1605]" captionTargetId="figure-184@174.[151,1436,189,1621]" captionTargetPageId="174" captionText="FIGURE 157. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–F MACN-Ar 19824: A. Abdomen, dorsal; B. Carapace, dorsal; C. Sternum, ventral; D. Cheliceral teeth, ventral; E. Rastellum, dorsal; F. Rastellum, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597573/files/figure.png" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Fig. 157 A</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1181,1386,1994,2020]" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Eyes: Diameters:</emphasis>
PME 0.2, PLE 0.48, ALE 0.6, AME 0.32; MOQ: Length 1.32, front width 3.48, back width 3; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1190,1369,2066,2092]" pageId="173" pageNumber="174">Interdistances:</emphasis>
PME–PME 1.88, PLE–PME 0.16, AME–AME 0.2, ALE–AME 1.04, ALE–PLE 0.64, AME–PME 0.68. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[619,777,1847,1874]" pageId="174" pageNumber="175">Ocular area:</emphasis>
OAL 5.12, OAW 4, and IF 3.25. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[529,600,1884,1910]" pageId="174" pageNumber="175">Body:</emphasis>
Clypeus: 0.37; Fovea: 2.62; Labium: long 1.5; wide 1.37; Chelicerae: long 3.37; wide 1.62; Sternum: long 5.12; wide 3.87. Abdomen: long 7.5; wide 5.62. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[512,750,1994,2020]" pageId="174" pageNumber="175">Leg measurements:</emphasis>
I: Fe 6.25/ Pa 2.62/ Ti 3.37/ Me 4.37/ Ta 2.5/ total 19.12. II: 5.62/ 2.87/ 2.62/ 4.25/ 2.5/ 17.87. III: 5/ 3.12/ 2.87/ 5/ 2.87/ 18.87. IV: 6.75/ 3.37/ 5.5/ 5.62/ 3.25/ 24.5. Formula 4123. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[881,1005,1847,1873]" pageId="174" pageNumber="175">Spination:</emphasis>
I—Fe v0, d0, p0, r0; Pa v0, d0, p0, r0; ti v0, d0, p0, r0; Me v1-2-2, d0, p1-0-3, r0; ta v0-2-0, d0, p0-2-2, r0. II—Fe v0, d0, p0, r0; Pa v0, d0, p0, r0; ti v2-2- 0, d0, p0, r0-4-4; Me v0-3-3, d0, p0-0-2, r0-2-5; ta v0-2-2, d0, p0-1-3, r0-1-3. III—Fe v0, d0, p0, r0; Pa v0, d5-7-30, p0-0-2, r0-0-1; ti v0, d1-0-16, p0-0-4, r1-0-3; Me v0-0-2, d2-0-1, p2-2-1, r0-1-6; ta v0, d0, p0, r0-0-4; IV—Fe v0, d0, p0, r0; Pa v0, d17-16-6, p0, r0; ti v0-1-3, d0, p1-0-3, r0; Me v3-3-4, d0-0-1, p2-3-4, r0-0-1; ta v0, d0, p3-5-4, r0. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[177,240,1402,1428]" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">Palp:</emphasis>
PA well developed. Embolus with three keels (PAc, PI and PS). BTA developed, dorsally displaced; Prolateral tegulum without cusps; PA continuous to PI; Embolar base thin (
<figureCitation box="[355,449,1514,1541]" captionStart="FIGURE 159" captionStartId="176.[136,235,1273,1297]" captionTargetBox="[187,1358,189,1237]" captionTargetId="figure-264@176.[151,1436,186,1249]" captionTargetPageId="176" captionText="FIGURE 159. Actinopus pindapoy sp. nov., male: A–C ZMB 19824: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597577/files/figure.png" pageId="175" pageNumber="176">Fig. 159</figureCitation>
A–C).
</paragraph>
